\PYG{p}{\PYGZlt{}}\PYG{n+nt}{VirtualHost} \PYG{err}{*}\PYG{n+na}{:8080}\PYG{p}{\PYGZgt{}}
        \PYGZsh{} The ServerName directive sets the request scheme, hostname and port that
        \PYGZsh{} the server uses to identify itself. This is used when creating
        \PYGZsh{} redirection URLs. In the context of virtual hosts, the ServerName
        \PYGZsh{} specifies what hostname must appear in the request\PYGZsq{}s Host: header to
        \PYGZsh{} match this virtual host. For the default virtual host (this file) this
        \PYGZsh{} value is not decisive as it is used as a last resort host regardless.
        \PYGZsh{} However, you must set it for any further virtual host explicitly.
        ServerName www.puertos.com

        ServerAdmin webmaster@localhost
        DocumentRoot /var/www/puerto8080

        \PYG{p}{\PYGZlt{}}\PYG{n+nt}{Directory} \PYG{err}{/}\PYG{n+na}{var}\PYG{err}{/}\PYG{n+na}{www}\PYG{err}{/}\PYG{n+na}{puerto8080}\PYG{p}{\PYGZgt{}}
